history.content:
You are either enrolled in the class or you are not.  Enrolling in the class means not being on the waitlist.  If you are on the waitlist for the lecture, you are not enrolled in the class and the discussion section you chose is the discussion section for which you are waitlisted.

A waitlist by definition is where students are placed who are not guaranteed enrollment.  Students who are guaranteed enrollment are enrolled.  Being on the waitlist means there is a chance you will be enrolled if either more TAs are hired and we have more capacity to enroll more students and/or students currently enrolled drop the class creating room for students who are on the waitlist to be moved in to take the spot they have created by leaving.
So I think I managed to enroll into a discussion, but I am 72 on the waitlist for 161. How does this work? Would I get into the class?  I am a declared cs major. Thank you.
history.subject: Enrolling in CS161
